Date: Thu 28 Feb 2008
Source: Ministerio da Saude, Secretaria de Vigilancia em Saude [in
Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://portal.saude.gov.br/portal/arquivos/pdf/boletimfa_280208.pdf>


Sylvan yellow fever in Brazil, 2007, 2008
-----------------------------------------
As of 28 Feb 2008, the [YF] epidemiological situation consisted of
notification of 60 suspected [and confirmed] cases of sylvan YF. Of
these, 35 cases were confirmed, of which 19 died (case fatality rate
of 54 percent). Another 23 cases were discarded as YF cases and 2
remain under investigation

The likely sites of [acquisition] of infection of these confirmed
cases occurred in forested areas of Goias, 60 percent (21 of 35) of
these cases, Mato Grosso do Sul 20 percent (7 of 35), Federal District
14 percent (5 of 35), and Mato Grosso 6 percent (2 of 35).

The distribution of cases and deaths from sylvan YF by date of onset
of symptoms shows the 1st confirmed case on 16 Dec 2007 and the latest
suspected case on 15 Feb 2008.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The bulletin reports one additional possible YF case and adds 2 more
confirmed cases over and above what they reported in the last weekly
bulletin (see ProMED-mail archive 20080228.0810), one each in Goias
and Mato Grosso do Sul states, and the last case a day later than
previously reported.

A map of Brazil showing the states mentioned, can be accessed at
<http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/brazil.jpg>. - Mod.TY]
